				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">It's slightly faster not to use X at all but instead to use the accumulator as a <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ring_counter" class="postlink">ring counter</a>. Load #$01 into A, and once the loop has run eight times, the 1 bit will have been rotated left into the carry flag where you can test for it with BCC. You can also get A more quickly by moving it in and out of Y (TYA = 2 cycles, TAY = 2 cycles) than by moving it in and out of the stack (PHA = 3 cycles, PLA = 4 cycles).</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

