						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">Dafydd wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">Trying to find an answer for 15 minutes, ask question, then find answer within seconds by myself. Why does this always happen?  <img src="./images/smilies/icon_redface.gif" alt=":oops:" title="Embarassed" /> <br /><br />Anyway, solution was to set <br /><div class="codetitle"><b>Code:</b></div><div class="codecontent">ROM:&nbsp; &nbsp; start = $C000, size = $4000, type = ro, file = %O, fill=yes, fillval=$00;</div></div><br />Another solution is to use start address $8000, like you used to have, and set the vectors to start from $BFFA. This works because when only 16KB of ROM is available, the lower 16KB page is mirrored from $8000-BFFF to $C000-FFFF.</div>

					
